org.jlibsedml

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlibsedml.SEDBase
      • org.jlibsedml.AbstractIdentifiableElement
        • org.jlibsedml.Model
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<AbstractIdentifiableElement>, IIdentifiable

    public final class Model
extends AbstractIdentifiableElement
    Encapsulates a SED-ML Model element. Note that this object is not the computational model itself, but holds information about the model within SED-ML.
    Author:
    anu/radams

        public Model(String id,
             String name,
             String language,
             String source)
        Parameters:
        id - - a unique identifier for the model within this SED-ML description.
        name - - optional, can be null.
        language - This should ideally be a URN, which may already be defined in SUPPORTED_LANGUAGE. If no language describes this model, the argument may be null.
        source - A mandatory URI to the model source.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if any argument except name is null or an empty string.

      • getSourceURI

        public URI getSourceURI()
                 throws URISyntaxException
        Gets the model's source description as a URI. How this object is interpreted is up to clients, but here are some examples that are likely to be common:
        • source="file.txt" A relative URI to a model file in the same folder as the SED-ML file.
        • source=http://www.cellml.org/models/ leloup_gonze_goldbeter_1999_version02 A URL to a model at a remote location.
        • source=urn:miriam:biomodels.db: BIOMD0000000003 A URN to a unique identifier for a model, which requires further resolution. Calling isOpaque() on this URI will return true.

        The following table may be helpful in using the java.net.URI API to resolve these values:

        String Authority Fragment Host Scheme Path Query
        /a/b/c.txt null null null file /a/b/c.txt null
        file.txt null null null null file.txt null
        urn:miriam:biomodels.db:BIOMD0000000003 null null null urn null null
        http://www.cellml.org/models/leloup_gonze_goldbeter_1999_version02 www.cellml.org null null http /models/leloup_gonze_goldbeter_1999_version02 null
        http://roedy@www.mindprod.com:80/products/abc.html?type=all&colour= brown #DEF roedy@www.mindprod.com:80 DEF roedy http /products/abc.html type=all&colour=brown
        Returns:
        A URI object
        Throws:
        URISyntaxException - if the value of the the 'source' attribute of a model element cannot be converted to a URI.

      • isSourceURIRelative

        public boolean isSourceURIRelative()
        Boolean test for whether the model source is a relative file location.
        Returns:
        true if this URI is a relative file location, false if URI is badly-formed or does not fulfill the criteria listed in table described in getSourceURI().
